.TH MULTIFLEXI-CLI 1 "May 2026" "MultiFlexi" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
multiflexi-cli \- MultiFlexi command-line interface for application and job management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B multiflexi-cli
[\fICOMMAND:ACTION\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B multiflexi-cli
is a Symfony Console-based command-line tool for managing MultiFlexi applications, jobs, users, tokens, companies, run-templates, credentials, queues, and more. It provides full CRUD operations and scheduling for all major MultiFlexi entities. Output can be formatted as text or JSON for automation and scripting.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B application:list / application:get / application:create / application:update / application:delete
Manage applications.
.RS
Options: --id, --uuid, --name, --description, --topics, --executable, --ociimage, --requirements, --homepage, --file, --appversion, --format
.RE
.TP
.B application:import-json / application:export-json / application:remove-json / application:validate-json
JSON import/export for applications.
.RS
Options: --id, --uuid, --file, --format
.RE
.TP
.B application:show-config
Show defined configuration fields for an application.
.RS
Options: --id, --uuid, --format
.RE
.TP
.B run-template:list / run-template:get / run-template:create / run-template:update / run-template:delete
Manage run templates.
.RS
Options: --id, --name, --app_id, --company_id, --interv, --active, --config, --format
.br
Task SLA options (create/update): --deadline_offset, --max_attempts, --retry_backoff (none|fixed|linear|exponential), --retry_min_gap, --allow_late
.RE
.TP
.B run-template:schedule
Schedule a run template as a job.
.RS
Options: --id, --schedule_time, --executor, --env (repeatable, one-time override not saved to run-template), --format
.br
Note: Only run-templates with active=1 can be scheduled.
.RE
.TP
.B run-template:assign-credential
Assign a credential to a run template.
.RS
Options: --runtemplate_id, --credential_id, --format
.RE
.TP
.B run-template:unassign-credential
Remove a credential assignment from a run template.
.RS
Options: --runtemplate_id, --credential_id, --format
.RE
.TP
.B run-template:list-credentials
List all credentials assigned to a run template.
.RS
Options: --runtemplate_id, --format
.RE
.TP
.B job:list / job:get / job:create / job:update / job:delete
Manage jobs.
.RS
Options: --id, --runtemplate_id, --scheduled, --executor, --schedule_type, --app_id, --limit, --offset, --order, --fields, --format
.br
--status filters: failed (exitcode != 0), success (exitcode = 0), running (started, not finished), pending (not yet started)
.RE
.TP
.B job:status
Show job status aggregation.
.RS
Options: --id, --format
.RE
.TP
.B task:list
List tasks (scheduling window obligations produced by RunTemplates).
.RS
Options: --runtemplate_id, --state (open|running|fulfilled|fulfilled_late|failed|missed), --limit, --offset, --order, --fields, --format
.RE
.TP
.B task:get
Get a task by ID.
.RS
Options: --id, --with-jobs (include job attempts), --fields, --format
.RE
.TP
.B task:status
Show aggregate task counts by state.
.RS
Options: --format
.RE
.TP
.B user:list / user:get / user:create / user:update / user:delete
Manage users.
.RS
Options: --id, --login, --email, --firstname, --lastname, --password, --plaintext, --enabled, --format
.RE
.TP
.B user-company:assign / user-company:unassign
Assign and unassign users to/from companies.
.RS
Options: --company_id, --user_id, --login, --email, --role (assign only), --format
.RE
.TP
.B user-role:set
Set RBAC roles for a user.
.RS
Options: --user_id, --login, --email, --roles, --replace, --assigned_by, --format
.RE
.TP
.B user-erasure:list / user-erasure:create / user-erasure:approve / user-erasure:reject / user-erasure:process / user-erasure:audit / user-erasure:cleanup
Manage GDPR user data erasure requests (Article 17 Right to Erasure).
.RS
Options: --user-id, --user-login, --request-id, --deletion-type, --reason, --notes, --force, --export-audit, --status, --format
.RE
.TP
.B token:list / token:get / token:create / token:generate / token:update / token:delete
Manage API tokens.
.RS
Options: --id, --user, --token, --format
.RE
.TP
.B company:list / company:get / company:create / company:update / company:remove
Manage companies.
.RS
Options: --id, --name, --customer, --enabled, --settings, --logo, --ic, --email, --slug, --format
.RE
.TP
.B company-app:list / company-app:assign / company-app:unassign
Manage company-application relations.
.RS
Options: --company_id, --app_id, --app_uuid, --limit, --offset, --order, --fields, --format
.RE
.TP
.B credential-type:list / credential-type:get / credential-type:create / credential-type:update / credential-type:delete
Manage credential types.
.RS
Options: --id, --uuid, --name, --format
.RE
.TP
.B credential-type:import-json / credential-type:export-json / credential-type:remove-json / credential-type:validate-json
JSON import/export for credential types.
.RS
Options: --id, --uuid, --file, --format
.RE
.TP
.B credential:list / credential:get / credential:create / credential:update / credential:remove
Manage credentials.
.RS
Options: --id, --name, --company-id, --credential-type-id, --fields, --format
.RE
.TP
.B event-source:list / event-source:get / event-source:create / event-source:update / event-source:remove / event-source:test
Manage event sources.
.RS
Options: --id, --name, --format
.RE
.TP
.B event-rule:list / event-rule:get / event-rule:create / event-rule:update / event-rule:remove
Manage event rules.
.RS
Options: --id, --event_source_id, --evidence, --operation, --runtemplate_id, --format
.RE
.TP
.B artifact:list / artifact:get / artifact:save
Manage job artifacts.
.RS
Options: --id, --job_id, --file, --fields, --format
.RE
.TP
.B encryption:status
Show encryption system status (master key, active keys, key details).
.RS
Options: --format
.RE
.TP
.B encryption:init
Re-initialize encryption keys (generates new 256-bit key encrypted with master key).
.RS
Options: --format
.br
Warning: Invalidates all previously encrypted credentials.
.RE
.TP
.B queue:overview
Show queue metrics and statistics.
.RS
Options: --format
.RE
.TP
.B queue:list
List scheduled jobs in the queue.
.RS
Options: --format, --limit, --order, --direction, --fields
.RE
.TP
.B queue:fix
Fix orphaned jobs and queue inconsistencies.
.TP
.B queue:truncate
Remove all scheduled jobs from the queue.
.TP
.B prune
Prune logs and jobs, keeping only the latest N records (default: 1000).
.RS
Options: --logs, --jobs, --keep
.RE
.TP
.B status
Show overall MultiFlexi system status (version, database, PHP, encryption, Zabbix, OpenTelemetry).
.RS
Options: --format
.RE
.TP
.B telemetry:test
Test OpenTelemetry metrics export.
.RS
Options: --endpoint, --disable-gauges
.RE
.TP
.B describe
List all available commands and their parameters.
.TP
.B completion
Dump the shell completion script for bash, zsh, or fish.
.RS
Arguments: shell (optional - bash, zsh, fish)
Options: --debug
.RE

.SH OPTIONS
Most commands support:
.TP
.BR -f ", " --format
Output format: text or json (default: text)
.TP
.BR --id
Specify record by numeric ID
.TP
.BR --uuid
Specify record by UUID (where supported)
.TP
.BR --help
Show help for a command
.TP
.BR --limit
Limit number of results (list commands)
.TP
.BR --offset
Offset for pagination (list commands)
.TP
.BR --order
Sort order: A (ascending) or D (descending)
.TP
.BR --fields
Comma-separated list of fields to display

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List all applications in JSON:
.B multiflexi-cli application:list -f json
.TP
Import application from JSON:
.B multiflexi-cli application:import-json --file=app.json
.TP
Schedule a run-template immediately:
.B multiflexi-cli run-template:schedule --id=167
.TP
Schedule with a one-time environment override (not saved to run-template):
.B multiflexi-cli run-template:schedule --id=167 --env=IMPORT_SCOPE=2025-11-01>2026-01-07
.TP
Assign a credential to a run template:
.B multiflexi-cli run-template:assign-credential --runtemplate_id=5 --credential_id=12
.TP
Remove a credential assignment from a run template:
.B multiflexi-cli run-template:unassign-credential --runtemplate_id=5 --credential_id=12
.TP
List credentials assigned to a run template:
.B multiflexi-cli run-template:list-credentials --runtemplate_id=5
.TP
List failed jobs:
.B multiflexi-cli job:list --status=failed
.TP
List pending jobs in JSON:
.B multiflexi-cli job:list --status=pending --format=json
.TP
Get job details:
.B multiflexi-cli job:get --id=123
.TP
Create a user:
.B multiflexi-cli user:create --login jsmith --email jsmith@example.com --plaintext secret
.TP
Generate a new token for user ID 2:
.B multiflexi-cli token:generate --user=2
.TP
Assign application to company:
.B multiflexi-cli company-app:assign --company_id=1 --app_id=5
.TP
Assign user to company:
.B multiflexi-cli user-company:assign --company_id=2 --login=jsmith --role=viewer
.TP
Unassign user from company:
.B multiflexi-cli user-company:unassign --company_id=2 --login=jsmith
.TP
Set RBAC roles for user:
.B multiflexi-cli user-role:set --login=jsmith --roles=admin,viewer --replace=true
.TP
Import credential type from JSON:
.B multiflexi-cli credential-type:import-json --file=credtype.json
.TP
Validate credential type JSON before import:
.B multiflexi-cli credential-type:validate-json --file=credtype.json
.TP
Show queue overview metrics:
.B multiflexi-cli queue:overview
.TP
List jobs ordered by scheduled time:
.B multiflexi-cli queue:list --order after --limit 10
.TP
Fix orphaned jobs:
.B multiflexi-cli queue:fix
.TP
Show encryption status:
.B multiflexi-cli encryption:status
.TP
Show system status in JSON:
.B multiflexi-cli status --format json
.TP
Prune logs and jobs, keeping the latest 500 records:
.B multiflexi-cli prune --logs --jobs --keep 500
.TP
List user deletion requests:
.B multiflexi-cli user-erasure:list --status=pending
.TP
Approve a deletion request:
.B multiflexi-cli user-erasure:approve --request-id=456 --notes="Approved by admin"
.TP
Show all available commands:
.B multiflexi-cli describe

